<BaseLayout title="About — Karuu"><section class="page-hero container about-hero"><p class="eyebrow">PERSONNEL FILE / 001</p><h1 class="about-name">Nguyễn Tiến Khang</h1><p class="about-summary">I am a Computer Science undergraduate focused on backend systems, cloud platforms, DevOps, and security-focused software. I build practical systems with clear architecture, measurable behavior, and thoughtful user-facing presentation. I am especially interested in work where reliability, observability, and well-defined constraints matter.</p></section><section class="section container"><div class="project-grid"><BrutalCard><MangaLabel>WHO I AM</MangaLabel><h2 style="margin-top:1.4rem">A systems-minded builder.</h2><p>I enjoy work that has a concrete operational shape: APIs that coordinate services, platforms that make infrastructure clearer, and security tools with thoughtful constraints.</p></BrutalCard><BrutalCard tone="yellow"><MangaLabel tone="pink">WHAT I BUILD</MangaLabel><h2 style="margin-top:1.4rem">Software with evidence.</h2><p>Backend services, cloud workflows, observability surfaces, and applied security experiments. I care about behavior you can inspect and architecture you can explain.</p></BrutalCard><BrutalCard tone="blue"><MangaLabel>CURRENT FOCUS</MangaLabel><h2 style="margin-top:1.4rem">Reliable boundaries.</h2><p>Container sandboxing, distributed workflows, runtime policy testing, and practical cloud delivery.</p></BrutalCard><BrutalCard tone="green"><MangaLabel>EDUCATION / DIRECTION</MangaLabel><h2 style="margin-top:1.4rem">Applied systems engineering.</h2><p>Building a portfolio of thesis-ready projects that bring together design, implementation, measurement, and technical communication.</p></BrutalCard></div></section></BaseLayout>
